ave control over how rigorous the cleaning cycle is. This certainly makes a cross-country road trip easier, reducing the need to hang clothes on a line. There&#39;s not too much choice in terms of drying your clothes with this one – you can set the time and designate the heat levels but that&#39;s about it. Other machines have more specific dryer options.","A major plus is that the machine does have automatic load sense, which means it limits the amount of water used if it senses there aren’t very many clothes in the load. This is extremely important, especially if you’re using water from an RV tank.","The door opens wide, yet the machine is still small enough to fit in a closet when it is not in use. It doesn’t have a lot of the features you find in washer dryer combos that are designed for year-round use in a home. For example, there aren’t special cycles for cleaning and sanitizing the machine, and you can’t set a delayed start. However, on the road these are likely not as important to you.","Parts and labor are covered by the usual one-year warranty, and the motor and wash drum are covered for the same amount of time. This is short, considering many of the bigger parts are covered up to the life of the product with the best washer dryer combos."]},"id":"88152d3f-c2cf-4d77-92b9-ed341a66924d","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"b23a15e2-6017-412c-82b6-bbbb58e611a3","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["While the Splendide is missing some of the convenience features we found on other machines, like delay wash, this may not be as important if you are using it in an RV where your washing is always on the go. This is a nice machine for RVs as it offers a level of convenience you don’t find often in an RV. This compact machine also would work well in apartments, condos and other living areas with limited space."]},"id":"3c5c05ab-c79c-4a3a-b0a5-1931cfbeab91","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_58682","url":"/splendide-review","au